      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VILLAROCK (9) has been hard to fault of late and made it two wins in a row when racing parked but toughing it out at his latest appearance at Penrith, getting home by 3 metres. Also did some work but was too strong at Menangle prior. Draws on the back line this time but if he gets the gaps can land the hat trick. CAPTAIN DORIAN (3) was solid when midfield in a higher-graded race at his latest appearance. Looks better placed having recorded a win and a second in his previous two outings here, both from wider barriers than this. JOGALONG BLUE (4) has been coming from the outside barrier at Menangle of late but gets his lowest draw for a long time and owns a good strike rate here, winning four of nine attempts. ULTIMATE TROUBLE (5) has been freshened since a fifth from a wider draw last start and recorded a string of placings prior. Must be respected.",
